# Carrier-BSP env consumed by stone-provision-tegraflash.sh.
#
# MIC-733-AO5A1 reuses the stock NVIDIA L4T `flash.sh jetson-agx-orin-devkit
# internal` flash profile (per Advantech's Flash SOP) — same flashvars
# layout, same .env.initrd-flash. Carrier customization is content-level:
# the files in this directory ship Advantech's modified DTB / BPMP DTB /
# pinmux / pad-voltage / GPIO defaults.
#
# Files are tagged with an `-adv` suffix to make their carrier origin
# explicit (vs. the stock NVIDIA filenames the MACHINE bakes). The
# CARRIER_FV_/CARRIER_ENV_ overrides below redirect the flash flow at
# those names, so the renames flow through tegraflash + initrd-flash
# without any other changes.
#
# Generic knob shape:
#   CARRIER_FV_<NAME>=value   → patches <NAME> in flashvars
#   CARRIER_ENV_<NAME>=value  → patches <NAME> in .env.initrd-flash
# See bsp/icam-540/stone/carrier-bsp/carrier.env for a worked example
# that also overrides CHECK_BOARDID / CHECK_BOARDSKU / SDRAM BCTs, and
# meta-avocado-nvidia/docs/adding-a-jetson-carrier.md for the full
# walkthrough.

CARRIER_LABEL="Advantech MIC-733-AO5A1 (Jetson AGX Orin SOM, P3701-0000)"

# Kernel DTB — Advantech adds carrier I/O nodes (two X550 PCIe NICs on
# C7/C8, USB hub, GPIO expanders, RS-232/422/485 chips) on top of the
# stock P3737 DTB. Our copy is now byte-identical to the vendor DTB
# (C8 left enabled); see the ODMDATA note below and the AO6A1 avocado.yaml.
CARRIER_ENV_DTBFILE="tegra234-p3737-0000+p3701-0000-nv-adv.dtb"

# BPMP DTB — use the unmodified upstream tegra234-bpmp-3701-0000-3737-0000.dtb.
# p3701.conf.common's board_sku 0000 selector picks it already, so no
# CARRIER_FV_BPFDTB_FILE override is needed.

# ODMDATA — UPHY lane brick mapping. THIS is what brings up the carrier's
# four 10GbE ports. They are NOT on-SoC MGBE: the carrier carries two Intel
# X550 dual-port NICs (8086:1563), one on PCIe controller C7 (141a0000) and
# one on C8 (141e0000), each an x8 controller (the X550 links at x4). The
# factory runtime DT and lsmod confirm all on-SoC MGBE/EQOS stay disabled;
# `ixgbe` drives all four ports.
#
# C8's PHYs are GBE-UPHY lanes. The stock meta-tegra agx-orin ODMDATA
# (gbe-uphy-config-22,...,hsio-uphy-config-0,gbe0-enable-10g) routes the GBE
# UPHY to the devkit's single on-SoC 10G MGBE and leaves C8's lanes
# unpowered — MB1 logs `W> Skipping GBE UPHY config`, and probing C8 then
# trips a fatal RAS UE at p2u_gbe_4 (0x3f600c0). An earlier revision worked
# around that by disabling pcie@141e0000 in the kernel DTB, which silently
# dropped X550 #2 (ports 3 & 4).
#
# The factory value below (verbatim from Advantech p3701.conf.common) routes
# the GBE UPHY's 8 lanes to PCIe C8 instead, powering X550 #2. The carrier
# UPHY-lane dtsi (tegra234-mb1-bct-uphylane-si.dtsi) is byte-identical to the
# avocado default, so no UPHY_CONFIG override is needed — only ODMDATA.
CARRIER_ENV_ODMDATA="gbe-uphy-config-0,hsstp-lane-map-3,nvhs-uphy-config-0,hsio-uphy-config-16"

# Pinmux / pad-voltage / GPIO dtsi — carrier-side, identical regardless
# of SOM SKU (the carrier exposes the same I/O whether the module is
# 32GB or 64GB). p3701.conf.common defaults all SKUs to the
# -p3701-0000-a04 family for these files, so the carrier-mod we ship
# applies to both AO5A1 and AO6A1 without further differentiation.
CARRIER_FV_PINMUX_CONFIG="tegra234-mb1-bct-pinmux-p3701-0000-a04-adv.dtsi"
CARRIER_FV_PMC_CONFIG="tegra234-mb1-bct-padvoltage-p3701-0000-a04-adv.dtsi"

# MB2 BCT misc DTS — disables the carrier (CVB) EEPROM read at I2C0
# slave 0xac. The MIC-733-AO carrier has no EEPROM at that address;
# without this override MB2 aborts in "Prepare eeprom data" with
# `I2C: slave not found in slaves` and busy-spins, never reaching the
# USB-storage stage of initrd-flash. Same fix Advantech ships in
# their vendor BSP's tegra234-mb2-bct-common.dtsi.
#
# NOTE: the flashvar name is `MB2BCT_CFG`, not `MB2_BCT`. The shell
# variable in p3701.conf.common is MB2_BCT, but L4T's flash framework
# exports it into the generated `flashvars` under the renamed key
# MB2BCT_CFG (see `flashvars` line `MB2BCT_CFG="..."`); patching
# anything other than that key produces a silent no-op WARNING.
CARRIER_FV_MB2BCT_CFG="tegra234-mb2-bct-misc-p3701-0000-adv.dts"

# EEPROM-comparison values — accept the AGX Orin 32GB SOM (P3701-0000).
# tegraflash aborts if the SOM's EEPROM-reported boardid/boardsku don't
# match these. The MIC-733-AO6A1 64GB variant uses 3701/0005; setting
# this explicitly here prevents a 64GB module from being misflashed
# with the 32GB carrier extension.
CARRIER_FV_CHECK_BOARDID="3701"
CARRIER_FV_CHECK_BOARDSKU="0000"
